title: [Cor'rah, Creeping Jungle]
description: Fallen leaves dot the rich soil in piles of no certain pattern, their wet, decaying presence adding a musty smell to the stale and humid air.  Flowers bloom from creeping vines wrapped around the trunks of various trees, their exotic hues providing a splash of striking color against the lush, verdant surroundings.  An occasional butterfly or hummingbird flutters near them, partaking of the sweet nectar they provide, before moving on to the next.
paths: Obvious paths: north, southeast, south, southwest
